The paper discusses the current state of Web APIs, which are commonly used in web development and fall under the category of World Wide Web (WWW) systems. The paper also analyzes the documentation of these APIs, which involves software engineering (SE) practices. Additionally, the paper touches upon issues related to distributed computing (DC) and security and privacy (SI) in the context of API authentication. Finally, the paper discusses the need for common standards and guidelines, which falls under the category of programming languages (PL).
